<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-6033] NoRedeliveryOnShutdown doesn&apos;t work for DeadLetterChannel</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-6033</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;See &lt;a href=&quot;http://camel.465427.n5.nabble.com/Wrong-test-for-allowRedeliveryWhileStopping-possible-bug-td5726184.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://camel.465427.n5.nabble.com/Wrong-test-for-allowRedeliveryWhileStopping-possible-bug-td5726184.html&lt;/a&gt; for details.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The assumption is if we use &quot;allowRedeliveryWhileStopping(false)&quot; in an error handler definition which use a dead letter channel, the message should be send to the configured dead letter channel if we are in a delivery by stopping Camel (instead of dropping the message).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12630535">CAMEL-6033</key>
            <summary>NoRedeliveryOnShutdown doesn&apos;t work for DeadLetterChannel</summary>
