                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13569604" author="muellerc" created="Sat, 2 Feb 2013 17:38:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I added a (slightly modified) unit test to show the bug: &lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/viewvc?view=revision&amp;amp;revision=1441777&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://svn.apache.org/viewvc?view=revision&amp;amp;revision=1441777&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
I added a @Ignore annotation so that the build will not fail.&lt;br/&gt;
It would be great if one of the key committer could have a look at it (I&apos;m too busy with other tasks).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13570101" author="davsclaus" created="Mon, 4 Feb 2013 10:32:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It was not designed to move the message to DLC, but reject redelivery during stopping/shutdown.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I will see what we can do to make this special case for DLC.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13570143" author="davsclaus" created="Mon, 4 Feb 2013 12:45:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have a potential solution. Though some tests in CXF now fails; will need to look into this. All other tests passes fine.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13570147" author="davsclaus" created="Mon, 4 Feb 2013 13:01:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Okay it was the CXF test that was wrong.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13570296" author="davsclaus" created="Mon, 4 Feb 2013 14:42:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;allowRedeliveryWhileStopping is a new option in Camel 2.11&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13570418" author="muellerc" created="Mon, 4 Feb 2013 17:33:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks Claus!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
